Class UpsightMonetizationIapEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.upsight.android.analytics.event.UpsightAnalyticsEvent<U,UpsightPublisherData>
      • com.upsight.android.analytics.internal.AnalyticsEvent<com.upsight.android.analytics.event.monetization.UpsightMonetizationIapEvent.UpsightData>
        • com.upsight.android.analytics.event.monetization.UpsightMonetizationIapEvent

  • public class UpsightMonetizationIapEvent
extends AnalyticsEvent<com.upsight.android.analytics.event.monetization.UpsightMonetizationIapEvent.UpsightData>
    This represents a purchase of virtual goods through an In App Purchase. A monetization.verified event will be generated as long as valid parameters are sent for store and iap_bundle, and the server is configured to verify the transaction with that particular store. While all optional parameters may be used for reporting within the monetization.iap event, they are not necessary for the generation of the monetization.verified event.

        Start building a UpsightMonetizationIapEvent.
        Parameters:
        store - The name of the store used for the IAP.
        iapBundle - Wrap the parameters necessary to validate the purchase in a json object. These values will be used server-side to validate the purchase with the corresponding store.
        totalPrice - The total price of the transaction, including fractional amounts of the currency, before store fees have been taken into account.
        price - The price per unit in local currency.
        quantity - The number of goods purchased.
        currency - The currency as a 3-character ISO 4217 code.
        product - The name of the product.
